{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775847212177,"sessionID":"ses_28742d97fffe2oXNNCTsjNslVt","part":{"id":"prt_d78bd908f001gCuE9fxaVZTNx7","messageID":"msg_d78bd783d001UCTx5q3GPTQJaJ","sessionID":"ses_28742d97fffe2oXNNCTsjNslVt","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-a41ee4be5c3045ef9af5c4235c8d7c79","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-008 Delta Spec\n\n[To be filled]","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-008/delta-spec.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-008/delta-spec.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-008/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775847212143,"end":1775847212176}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775847212180,"sessionID":"ses_28742d97fffe2oXNNCTsjNslVt","part":{"id":"prt_d78bdf196001kVmqGT6cYMiAVM","messageID":"msg_d78bd783d001UCTx5q3GPTQJaJ","sessionID":"ses_28742d97fffe2oXNNCTsjNslVt","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-edd2dc47282e4aa3953136e3d5057b6f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-008 Design — Sandbox GC 定时清理机制\n\n**Module**: `pkg/workloadmanager`\n**Language**: Go\n**Size**: S\n**Purpose**: Implement a scheduled garbage collection mechanism for sandbox resources to clean up unused or expired sandboxes.\n\n## Overview\n\nThis AR implements a scheduled garbage collection mechanism that periodically identifies and cleans up sandbox resources that are no longer in use or have exceeded their TTL. This helps prevent resource leaks and reduces operational overhead.\n\n### Key Requirements\n\n- Periodic scanning of sandbox resources\n- Identify sandboxes with expired TTL or no active sessions\n- Clean up orphaned sandbox resources\n- Configurable GC schedule and TTL thresholds\n- Graceful deletion with proper finalizer handling\n- Logging and metrics for GC operations\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Package Structure\n\n```\npkg/workloadmanager/gc/\n├── scheduler.go       # GC scheduler implementation\n├── collector.go       # GC collector logic\n├── policy.go          # GC policy and rules\n└── metrics.go         # GC metrics\n```\n\n### Component Interactions\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                      GC Scheduler                                │\n│                                                                  │\n│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n│  │              GC Policy Engine                             │   │\n│  │  - Determine sandboxes eligible for GC                   │   │\n│  │  - Apply TTL and activity checks                          │   │\n│  │  - Filter by namespace and labels                        │   │\n│  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n│                                                                  │\n│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n│  │              GC Collector                                 │   │\n│  │  - Identify candidate sandboxes                           │   │\n│  │  - Delete sandbox resources                              │   │\n│  │  - Clean up associated metadata                          │   │\n│  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n           │                     │                     │\n           │                     │                     │\n           ▼                     ▼                     ▼\n┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐\n│  Kubernetes API  │  │     Redis        │  │   Metrics/Logs   │\n│  (client-go)     │  │  (session store) │  │                  │\n│  - Sandbox CR    │  │  - Session TTL   │  │  - GC counters   │\n│  - Status updates│  │  - Metadata      │  │  - Duration      │\n└──────────────────┘  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────────┘\n```\n\n### GC Flow\n\n```\nGC Schedule Triggered\n    ↓\n[Policy Check] Apply GC policy rules\n    ↓\n[Candidate Selection] Identify sandboxes for GC\n    ↓\n[Eligibility Check] Verify TTL and activity\n    ↓\n[Finalizer Check] Ensure safe deletion\n    ↓\n[Resource Deletion] Delete sandbox and metadata\n    ↓\n[Metric Update] Record GC operation metrics\n    ↓\n[Logging] Log GC operation details\n    ↓\n[Return] Wait for next schedule\n```\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### GC Scheduler\n\n```go\n// GCScheduler manages the garbage collection schedule\ntype GCScheduler struct {\n    client.Client\n    Store       store.Store\n    Config      *GCConfig\n    Logger      logr.Logger\n    Recorder    record.EventRecorder\n\n    // Schedule configuration\n    Interval    time.Duration\n    StopCh      chan struct{}\n}\n\n// GCConfig provides configuration for garbage collection\ntype GCConfig struct {\n    // Interval is the GC run interval\n    Interval time.Duration\n\n    // MaxAge is the maximum age for sandboxes\n    MaxAge time.Duration\n\n    // IdleTimeout is the idle timeout for inactive sandboxes\n    IdleTimeout time.Duration\n\n    // DryRun enables dry run mode\n    DryRun bool\n\n    // Namespaces restricts GC to specific namespaces\n    Namespaces []string\n\n    // LabelSelector filters by labels\n    LabelSelector string\n}\n```\n\n### GC Collector\n\n```go\n// GCCollector performs garbage collection operations\ntype GCCollector struct {\n    client.Client\n    Config      *GCConfig\n    Logger      logr.Logger\n    Metrics     *GCMetrics\n}\n\n// GCPolicy defines garbage collection policy\ntype GCPolicy struct {\n    // MaxAgeThreshold is the maximum age threshold\n    MaxAgeThreshold time.Duration\n\n    // IdleThreshold is the idle activity threshold\n    IdleThreshold time.Duration\n\n    // OrphanPolicy determines how to handle orphaned resources\n    OrphanPolicy OrphanPolicy\n}\n\n// OrphanPolicy defines orphan handling policy\ntype OrphanPolicy string\n\nconst (\n    OrphanPolicyDelete    OrphanPolicy = \"delete\"\n    OrphanPolicyKeep      OrphanPolicy = \"keep\"\n    OrphanPolicyReconcile OrphanPolicy = \"reconcile\"\n)\n\n// GCResult represents the result of a GC operation\ntype GCResult struct {\n    Scanned     int\n    Candidates  int\n    Deleted     int\n    Errors      int\n    Duration    time.Duration\n}\n```\n\n### GC Metrics\n\n```go\n// GCMetrics tracks garbage collection metrics\ntype GCMetrics struct {\n    RunsTotal        prometheus.Counter\n    DeletedTotal     prometheus.Counter\n    ErrorsTotal      prometheus.Counter\n    Duration         prometheus.Histogram\n    Candidates       prometheus.Gauge\n}\n```\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### GC Scheduler Interface\n\n```go\n// Start starts the GC scheduler\nfunc (s *GCScheduler) Start(ctx context.Context) error\n\n// Stop stops the GC scheduler\nfunc (s *GCScheduler) Stop()\n\n// RunOnce runs GC once (for testing)\nfunc (s *GCScheduler) RunOnce(ctx context.Context) (*GCResult, error)\n```\n\n### GC Collector Interface\n\n```go\n// Collect performs garbage collection\nfunc (c *GCCollector) Collect(ctx context.Context) (*GCResult, error)\n\n// FindCandidates finds sandboxes eligible for GC\nfunc (c *GCCollector) FindCandidates(ctx context.Context) ([]*unstructured.Unstructured, error)\n\n// Delete deletes a sandbox resource\nfunc (c *GCCollector) Delete(ctx context.Context, sandbox *unstructured.Unstructured) error\n```\n\n### GC Policy Interface\n\n```go\n// ShouldGC determines if a sandbox should be garbage collected\nfunc (p *GCPolicy) ShouldGC(sandbox *unstructured.Unstructured, sessionInfo *SessionInfo) bool\n\n// IsExpired checks if a sandbox has expired based on TTL\nfunc (p *GCPolicy) IsExpired(sandbox *unstructured.Unstructured) bool\n\n// IsIdle checks if a sandbox is idle based on activity\nfunc (p *GCPolicy) IsIdle(sandbox *unstructured.Unstructured, sessionInfo *SessionInfo) bool\n```\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\nTest GC policy logic, candidate selection, and deletion operations.\n\n### Integration Tests\n\nTest GC operations in a real Kubernetes environment with envtest.\n\n## Documentation\n\n### Configuration\n\n```yaml\n# GC configuration\ngc:\n  # GC run interval\n  interval: \"5m\"\n\n  # Maximum age for sandboxes\n  maxAge: \"24h\"\n\n  # Idle timeout for inactive sandboxes\n  idleTimeout: \"1h\"\n\n  # Dry run mode\n  dryRun: false\n\n  # Namespaces to process (empty = all)\n  namespaces: []\n\n  # Label selector\n  labelSelector: \"\"\n```\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n- [ ] GC scheduler runs periodically\n- [ ] Orphaned sandboxes are identified and cleaned up\n- [ ] Expired sandboxes are deleted\n- [ ] Metrics are recorded for GC operations\n- [ ] Logging provides visibility into GC operations\n- [ ] Unit tests cover GC logic\n- [ ] Integration tests validate GC operations","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-008/design.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-008/design.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-008/design.md","time":{"start":1775847212146,"end":1775847212178}}}}
